sentences: Natalia Sokolovskaya (Russian: Наталья Соколовская; born in June, 1989) is a Russian pianist and composer.
She studied at the Moscow Conservatory from 2007-13.
Since her first solo recital in 2003, she has given many recitals in the UK, Australia, Germany, Austria, France, Italy, Spain, Czech Republic, Taiwan, Russia and Malta.
She released a 2017 album of Piano Works by Leoš Janáček.
She also appeared on Guy Bacos's 2017 albums Christmas Variations and Mourning, Elegy, and Others.
